cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

This paper discusses the design and optimization of a wireless powered multiuser mobile-edge computing system, which involves wireless power transfer, computation offloading, and resource allocation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which covers topics related to wireless communication, network protocols, and mobile computing. The paper also involves optimization techniques and information theory, which suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the energy consumption and resource allocation, which are relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
